<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Esaki" authorityYear="1926" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Metrocoris tenuicornis" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenuicornis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">Metrocoris tenuicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Esaki, 1926 (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Esaki, T." journalOrPublisher="Annales Historico-naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" pagination="117 - 164" refId="B5982045" refString="Esaki, T., 1926. The water-striders of the subfamily Halobatinae in the Hungarian National Museum. Annales Historico-naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici 23: 117 - 164" title="The water-striders of the subfamily Halobatinae in the Hungarian National Museum" volume="23" year="1926">Esaki 1926</bibRefCitation>
) (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F5979086" captionText="Figure 9. Selected habitus illustrations of Gerromorpha of Mindoro A. Limnogonus nitidus; B. Limnometra nigripennis nigripennis; C. Tenagogonus sp. (mutilated specimen); D. Rheumatogonus luzonicus; E. Metrocoris tenuicornis. Scale bars 10 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.8.e56883.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/467156" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">9</figureCitation>
E) is a widspread species in western India, southern China, mainland southeast Asia, Sumatra, Java and Borneo, but only known so far from Mindoro and Greater Palawan, in the Philippines (
<bibRefCitation author="Chen, P. P." journalOrPublisher="Steenstrupia" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" pagination="1 - 82" refId="B5978710" refString="Chen, P. P., Nieser, N., 1993. A taxonomic revision of the Oriental water strider genus Metrocoris Mayr (Hemiptera, Gerridae) Part I and II. Steenstrupia 19: 1 - 82" title="A taxonomic revision of the Oriental water strider genus Metrocoris Mayr (Hemiptera, Gerridae) Part I and II" volume="19" year="1993">Chen and Nieser 1993</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Freitag, Hendrik" journalOrPublisher="Philippine Journal of Systematic Biology" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" pagination="54 - 80" refId="B5979143" refString="Freitag, Hendrik, Zettel, Herbert, 2012. Aquatic Heteroptera of the Lake Manguao catchment, Palawan and new rank of Rhagovelia kawakamii hoberlandti Hungerford &amp; Matsuda, 1961. Philippine Journal of Systematic Biology 6: 54 - 80" title="Aquatic Heteroptera of the Lake Manguao catchment, Palawan and new rank of Rhagovelia kawakamii hoberlandti Hungerford &amp; Matsuda, 1961" volume="6" year="2012">Freitag and Zettel 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
