<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" type="habitat">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">Habitat</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">
Quiet bays of smoothly-flowing streams and the edge of large rocks in the middle of streams are the preferred habitats of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1865" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Metrocoris" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">Metrocoris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Mayr, 1865 species (
<bibRefCitation author="Chen, P. P." journalOrPublisher="Steenstrupia" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" pagination="1 - 82" refId="B5978710" refString="Chen, P. P., Nieser, N., 1993. A taxonomic revision of the Oriental water strider genus Metrocoris Mayr (Hemiptera, Gerridae) Part I and II. Steenstrupia 19: 1 - 82" title="A taxonomic revision of the Oriental water strider genus Metrocoris Mayr (Hemiptera, Gerridae) Part I and II" volume="19" year="1993">Chen and Nieser 1993</bibRefCitation>
), such as the records presented here (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F5979090" captionText="Figure 8. Distribution of the collecting sites of Gerromorpha material (part 2) treated in this study." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.8.e56883.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/467248" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">8</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
